cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL 

The paper deals with games on graphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and the study of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). The paper also discusses memory requirements and winning strategies, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes subclasses of generalized reachability games, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
